bio.experienceSummary:
Hello there! 

I'm an English and Portuguese Teacher from Brazil, and I've just relocated back to the U. S. I absolutely love working with kids and I look forward connecting with you.

- Previous English/Portuguese Teacher in Brazil. 
- Four years of experience as a nanny in NYC - great references. 
- Two Bachelor's degrees: Marketing and Teaching (English) 
- Fluent in three languages: English, Portuguese and Spanish.
- Previous experience teaching English at Language, Elementary and High School in Brazil.
- Previous experience with learning disabilities and special needs children.
- Happy to cook healthy meals, help with homework, do light housekeeping, shopping, run errands, laundry, overnight care and pet care.
- Other skills: great cook, patient, loving, active, calm, engaging, punctual, responsible, reliable, flexible, organized, clean and strong swimmer.
- Able to navigate NYC subway and take the kids wherever they need to go.

description.originalText: Leticia was great with my son who has adhd.  She is patient, kind and sweet.  Leticia also did light housekeeping which was a lifesaver for me each day as well as walking our dog.  I never write reviews but she was really wonderful!

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello! My name is Amina, and I am an artist and educator with a rich background in both the arts and child care. I hold degrees from the School of the Art Institute of Chicago and the Yale School of Art. Over the years, I have dedicated myself to providing compassionate, attentive, and creative child care and education.
My experience spans from working with young learners aged 3 to 17 in various settings, including art centers and contemporary art museums. Additionally, I have over four years of teaching experience in academic environments where I focus on nurturing creativity and a love of learning in every child.
I am known for my playful, nurturing approach, and I deeply value kindness and compassion in my interactions. My goal is to collaborate with progressive, thoughtful families who are interested in a holistic approach to childcare, where creativity and personal growth are at the forefront.

Being around kids is truly magnificent and is a big passion of mine. I graduated from Northeastern University with a degree in Education and childhood psychology. All together, I have been working for over 6 years, being everything from an infant/toddler nanny to a nanny for children from 4 months-13, to working with children in an orphanage, to a camp counselor, to a dance instructor, to a children's yoga instructor. I am a big believer that kids are so much more capable than what most people believe they are, and it's never too early to introduce life lessons and important skills!

Hello! My name is Harolynn and I am a 26-year-old nanny with 6 years of part-time experience working with children. As a recent college graduate, I am excited to pursue my passion for caring for others by returning to school to study nursing, with plans to specialize in pediatric care in the NICU. My experience as a nanny has allowed me to develop strong skills in creating nurturing and safe environments where children can thrive, learn, and grow. I have a true passion for engaging children in creative activities, supporting outdoor play, and encouraging them to reach their developmental milestones. I believe in providing a balanced, loving environment where children can explore their curiosity and feel safe and supported. I would love the opportunity to contribute to your family's well-being, offering you peace of mind while caring for your little ones.

Dear family,
Greetings! To begin, I'm from the Philippines. I started full-time job as Nanny for a 6-month-old boy in 2016 then another 2nd baby in the year of 2017. Being a nanny doesn't limit my capacity to do chores, doing dishes, laundry and tidying esp the bedroom and playroom of the kids. Sept of 2018, I have to leave the family, as I'm preparing myself to be a mom. After few months of giving birth I get back to work as part time nanny/ housekeeper for 2 families. I find my work very rewarding and thus, I am committed to provide a happy, positive and nurturing environment for the family in my care. Also, I took courses on Caregiver lessons and was teaching Reading and Writing to kindergarten students on summer and school breaks. I find my work very rewarding and thus, I am committed to provide a happy, positive and nurturing environment for the children in my care. Working with kids, gives me the feeling of still being close to my own kid.

I have two years of experience taking care of my niece (who is 2 years old). I also have a good amount of experience babysitting a close friend's kids (who were 5 and 2 at the time). I really enjoy being around kids and am very responsible and reliable.

I have a passion for healthy cooking and baking. I'm great at planning fun activities to do with kids, whether it's watching a movie with popcorn or painting/drawing. I've completed my undergraduate degree at Baruch college in operations management. I've worked with children at a day care in the past, as a nutritionist assistant, and currently work in jewelry. I'm very nurturing, patient, maternal, empathetic, kind, respectful, organized, educated, and experienced :) I have 3 years of experience in caregiving.

Hi, I'm Alexandra! 

I have over 10 years experience caring for children from infancy through adolescence. I have cared for children as a babysitter, camp counselor and department director, in a daycare setting and while teaching social emotional learning to children in primary school. 

I am patient, calm, creative, imaginative, and friendly. I value open communication with parents and follow their preferred methods to discuss their child's day or any concerns that arise. My passion lies in fostering children's growth and development, and I strive to make a positive impact on their lives. 

I am comfortable enforcing household rules and enjoy playing a variety of games with children, being creative and coordinating other fun activities. 

With my diverse educational background and fluency in English, French, and German, I am well-equipped to provide a nurturing and stimulating environment for your children.

description.originalText: Alexandra is so great! She is very thoughtful, kind, creative and caring. She often came in with an activity planned that matched my little one’s interests and took him to exciting outings that he later talked about with joy. She was very thoughtful and empathetic towards our child’s specific needs emotionally, and was understanding and patient with him, while still remaining responsible. He loved her and I’m very grateful that we found such a reliable and kind caregiver. Thank you Alex!

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello! I spent the past five years teaching special education in Williamson County, TN, and am now gearing up to obtain a graduate degree in educational leadership at at Columbia University in the Fall.
I am in Nashville through the end of August, then will be based in NYC. I have experience in both full-time nannying and part-time babysitting positions, working with children at infancy, through high school. I have experience working with children both typically developing and with minor to significant disabilities, in a variety of settings. Additionally, I have a successful private tutoring business for students with disabilities. I absolutely love being around children and fostering relationships with families in the process. I am CPR and First-Aid certified, and have been background checked.

description.displayText: Hannah is the best. She was our nanny for 4 months, full time, and it was a dream. She nannied our then 2 year old and 5 month old. Our 5 month old was a very tough baby and she was so patient and stuck with every new sleeping program we threw her way with grace. It was also during COVID, so she was home with the girls while we were working from home in a small house. She made the situation absolutely comfortable for all parties and we loved having her there. She still babysits for us and feels like a part of our family!

bio.experienceSummary:
Ready for hire immediately! 

I've been a nanny for over a decade and have experience working with all ages. I've worked with up to 6 children at a time and I'm confident in my abilities to manage and entertain. 


I have a Bachelor of Fine Arts in Musical Theatre from Oakland University.
I'm pursuing acting so would love to have a family who's open to me attending auditions and performances. 

Please let me know if you have any questions, and I look forward to hearing from you!
